  <original-body>At the moment link_to :method =&gt; ... creates JavaScript that appends a FORM to the document (and then submits it). Form is appended as a sibling of link element, so if you use link_to :method =&gt; ... within a form, you'll get nested FORM elements, which is explicitly prohibited by specification [1].
The solution is to append the form to BODY element, which should guarantee, that we don't nest forms.

[1] http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/#prohibitions</original-body>
